#333399>(6/12/01 9:09:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tremor?</span><hr size=1> For the last 3 days, I've been grouping in Sol A, multiple goblin pulls. Decided to try out Tremor to knock some HPs off those gobs. When I cast it, I don't get any message about them taking damage. Is this the way it's supposed to work, like the DoT spells don't show you the damage? Or am I doing something wrong, i.e. not close enough to mobs, etc?<br>
<br>
Murias Leafstorm<br>
25th Druid of Tunare<br>
Druzzil Ro<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unuther1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nuther1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 9:58:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> tremor</span><hr size=1> Are you standing right in the middle of the mobs?<br>
<br>
I would like to try this spell to, but I think I would wear a damage shield first, then tremor, then pogonip or vs versa.<br>
<br>
What if it was 2-3 mobs, you could root them, then tremor, then they wouldnt be able to chase you down and smack you.<br>
<br>
fun, fun <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rtfm>rtfm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 10:08:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: tremor</span><hr size=1> Pogonip will hit you if you try that.<br>
<br>
And its expensive.<br>
<br>
If you root, most likely(for the rain spell) it will break on the first wave.<br>
<br>
Save both for an Area of Effect party, if you don't mind exploiting that is.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubuzwat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Buzwat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 10:43:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tremor</span><hr size=1> In Blackburrow I was killing gnolls trying to get teeth to raise Steel Worker faction.  Well after a while I got bored and memed tremor.  Well low an behold some lvl 10 player trained about 5 gnolls to me so I hit Tremor got a message saying gnoll takes x amount of damage and 5 gnolls dropped dead.  Well next thing I know a couple of groups pull trains to the bottom of the stairs where I am sitting I stand hit tremor and about 15 gnolls drop and 5 run off.  I aslways get  message and faction.  Well after that we start paying people to train us it was non stop fun till our kill rate was faster then the spawn rate.  But we always got a message.<br>
First time I tried tremor I was in Misty at one of the gob camps and nada they have to be on top of you for it to work.<br>
<br>
Cheers<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujenesagara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jene Sagara</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 12:09:05 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/877/45/28774560.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tremor</span><hr size=1> I believe that tremor, earthquake and upheaval are all self radiating...<br>
<br>
meaning you have to be in melee contact for the spells to hit all the targets, I love it when we have to camp greenies for quest items, i tell them to pull lots and I use these 3 spells lined up to just maul everything, but you have to be in the center of the mobs. <p><HR SIZE=2 WIDTH="50%" ALIGN=CENTER><P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="Teal"><FONT SIZE=2><b><A HREF="http://sr.crypticmission.net/brell/players.cgi?view=0079">Jene Sagara</A></u><BR>Nature Goddess<BR><A HREF="http://pub70.ezboard.com/bdracaena">~Dracaena Arcanum~</A><BR><blink>..:*:...Brell Serilis...:*:..</blink></P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uirontreeravenstrike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Irontree Ravenstrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 4:38:34 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~carriedingus/irontree.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tremor?</span><hr size=1> What is the exploit i keep hearing about with rain spells?<br>
<br>
You said if you don't mind exploiting?<br>
<br>
What are you talking about? <p><IMG SRC  = "http://home.earthlink.net/~carriedingus/line.gif"><BR><BR>
